// Vector network encoding and path conversion
// Serialises and deserialises VectorNetwork data to/from a compact binary blob format, converts networks to CanvasKit Path objects (handling both region-based and open-chain paths), and computes axis-aligned bounding boxes including bezier control points.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

Binary blob layout:
  Header:  [numVertices:u32, numSegments:u32, numRegions:u32]  (12 bytes)
  Vertex:  [styleOverrideIdx:u32, x:f32, y:f32]               (12 bytes each)
  Segment: [styleOverrideIdx:u32, start:u32, tsX:f32, tsY:f32, end:u32, teX:f32, teY:f32]  (28 bytes each)
  Region:  [windingRule:u32, numLoops:u32, {numSegs:u32, segIdx...}...]  (variable)

FUNCTION decodeVectorNetworkBlob(data, styleOverrideTable?) -> VectorNetwork [2026-03-26]  EXPORT
  Reads the binary blob using DataView, deserialising header counts, then vertex positions (with handleMirroring from style overrides), segment start/end indices and tangent offsets, and region winding rules and loop segment index arrays.

---

FUNCTION encodeVectorNetworkBlob(network: VectorNetwork) -> Uint8Array [2026-03-26]  EXPORT
  Calculates the exact buffer size needed, allocates an ArrayBuffer, and writes header, vertex, segment, and region data in the binary format described above.

---

FUNCTION vectorNetworkToPath(ck, network) -> Path [2026-03-26]          EXPORT
  If the network has regions, traces each region's loops as closed sub-paths with the correct fill type. If there are no regions, builds open chains via buildChains (preferring degree-1 endpoint vertices), then draws any remaining disconnected segments.

---

FUNCTION addLoopToPath(path, loop, segments, vertices) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Moves to the first vertex of the loop, appends each segment via addSegmentToPath, and closes the path if the last segment ends at the start vertex.

---

FUNCTION addSegmentToPath(path, seg, vertices) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Draws a straight lineTo if both tangent offsets are zero, otherwise draws a cubic bezier using tangent offsets as control point displacements from the start and end vertices.

---

FUNCTION buildChains(segments, _vertexCount) -> number[][] [2026-03-26]
  Builds an adjacency map of vertex-to-segment connections. Traverses chains starting from degree-1 vertices (open endpoints); falls back to any unvisited start vertex. Returns an array of ordered segment-index arrays representing connected paths.

---

FUNCTION computeVectorBounds(network) -> { x, y, width, height } [2026-03-26]  EXPORT
  Iterates all vertices and bezier control points to compute the axis-aligned bounding box of the entire network including curve bulge.
